{
  "//": "Rookie-season texture batch, Sonnet 5. Originally written against the stale StartingAge-19 premise -- EVERY event here now additionally requires { \"field\": \"tier\", \"op\": \">=\", \"value\": 2 } (MinorA and above), so this professional-clubhouse content is unreachable at HS (0) or College (1) tier regardless of rookie_settled. This is the fix for the bug the HS onboarding arc's design doc (docs/design/hs_onboarding_events.md) diagnosed: a 16-year-old freshman (CareerManager.StartingAge 16 since the grade-system pass) was receiving 'Welcome to the show, kid', rookie karaoke, a first pro paycheck, and motel road trips starting day 2, because clubhouse_welcome's only prerequisite was flag_inactive rookie_settled. rookie_settled remains the intra-batch entry gate, now AND-ed with the tier floor -- every event self-gates, not just the entry, so a save that already fired clubhouse_welcome pre-fix (rookie_settled active on an HS/College avatar) heals with zero DB surgery: a contaminated avatar below tier 2 simply never satisfies any rookie event again. The avatar only reaches tier 2 after graduating HS -> College -> signing a pro deal, at which point this batch's low-stakes clubhouse/coach/homesickness/paycheck content (originally: closes the gap Fable 5's Phase-12e review flagged, that a fresh pro avatar satisfied zero prerequisites in core_events.json/career_arc_events.json/marriage_and_family_events.json for its first two full seasons) resumes exactly as designed. scope:'avatar' throughout (not 'any') is deliberate: it restricts evaluation to the single played character instead of diluting fire chances across every rostered NPC, the same call marriage_and_family_events.json already made for personal-arc content. cashed_first_check -> spent_the_check/frugal_rookie -> splurge_callback/frugal_callback is a two-step paycheck cascade, the same min_days_since-paced pattern as core_events.json's bribe->shakedown and marriage_and_family_events.json's married->expecting, just paced in weeks instead of years. Every set_flag here is read by at least one prerequisite (several self-referentially, the documented once-ever idiom) -- no orphans, no dead-end forward hooks, fully self-contained per check_event_graph_integrity #2/#3. Disclosed limitations: (1) in_a_slump/on_a_heater are flavor-only -- ConditionEvaluator has no read access to recent PA outcomes, so these fire on weight/cooldown, not actual performance; a real hot/cold streak field would need a new poll column. (2) No 'interest' consequences anywhere in this batch -- the avatar's baseball_interest starts at the 100 ceiling (CareerManager avatar creation), so any interest delta on an avatar-scope event clamps to a no-op; that writer stays reserved for the heir-interest content backyard_catch/benched_for_video_games already own.",
